Function: strsplit
Section: programming/specific
C-Name: strsplit
Prototype: GDG
Help: strsplit(s,{p = ""}): splits the string s into a vector of strings, with
 p acting as a delimiter between successive fields; if p is empty or omitted,
 split into characters.
Doc: splits the string $s$ into a vector into a vector of strings, with $p$
 acting as a delimiter. If $p$ is empty or omitted, split the string into
 characters.
 \bprog
 ? strsplit("abc::def::ghi", "::")
 %1 = ["abc", "def", "ghi"]

 ? strsplit("abc", "")
 @eprog
